{
  "texts": [
    "Thus one could ask, for any ρ ∈ L ∞ (Q), is there a Lipschitz vector field π satisfying (1.1) a.e.?",
    "The only available result in this direction is due to Burago and Kleiner [11] and independently McMullen [33], who, provided d ≥ 2, construct a ρ ∈ L ∞ (Q) attaining only two positive values such that there is no biLipschitz solution to the equation.",
    "We give a stronger result, asserting that the of set of ρ ∈ L ∞ (Q) for which there exists a Lipschitz solution (as opposed to biLipschitz) is \"small\" (Proposition 1.5).It is this property of the prescribed Jacobian equation that eventually leads to the resolution of Lang's Flat Chain Conjecture.",
    "A number of connections of the conjecture to a Lipschitz regularity of PDEs have been recently observed by multiple groups [5,8,19,32] independently (including the author), as is also indicated in the recent survey by Marchese [31].",
    "We provide a more detailed discussion of these connections in Subsection 1.3."
  ]
}